ir desire for full citizenship, the complex loyalties that shaped their actions, and the inspiring and heartbreaking results of their choices-- choices that still echo through the United States today. Contributors: Stephen D. Engle, William McKee Evans, David T. Gleeson, Andrea Mehrländer, Joseph P. Reidy, Robert N. Rosen, and Susannah J. Ural.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aImmigrantszUnited StatesxSocial conditionsy19th century. 0aMinoritieszUnited StatesxSocial conditionsy19th century. 4aAmerica. 4aAnglo-Saxon. 4aCitizens. 4aCivil. 4aGrounded. 4aProtestant. 4abook. 4acitizenry. 4adominant. 4aeffort. 4aexperiences. 4aexperts. 4aextensive. 4afields. 4afirst. 4agather. 4ainto. 4alived. 4anineteenth-century. 4aoutside. 4apopulations. 4aresearch. 4arespective. 4atheir. 4atogether. 4awartime. 4awhite. 7aHISTORY / United States / Civil War Period (1850-1877).2bisacsh1 aUral, Susannah J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP Backlist 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814785737423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814785737.jpg  a978-3-11-070644-4  NYUP Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK